  <para>
    The <classname>CircleBrush</classname> is used when selecting
    pixels with the <link
    linkend="MenuItem-OOF.Graphics_n.Toolbox.Pixel_Select.Brush"><classname>Brush</classname></link>
    selection tool in the <link
    linkend="Section-Graphics-PixelSelection">Pixel Selection</link>
    toolbox.  It selects all pixels within a distance
    <varname>radius</varname> of the mouse.  The
    <varname>radius</varname> is given in <link
    linkend="Section-Concepts-Microstructure-Coordinates"><emphasis>physical</emphasis></link>
    units.
  </para>
  <figure id="Figure-CircleBrush">
    <title>Selection with a Circular Brush</title>
    <mediaobject>
      <imageobject>
	<imagedata fileref="FIGURES/pixelselect/circlebrush.png"
	  format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
      <imageobject>
	<imagedata fileref="FIGURES/pixelselect/circlebrush.eps"
	  format="EPS"/>
      </imageobject>
      <caption>
	<simpara>
	  A selection made with the circular brush, with
	  <varname>radius</varname>=15.  The physical size of the
	  &micro; is 200&times;200.  Compare with the square brush in
	  <xref linkend="Figure-SquareBrush"/>.
	</simpara>
      </caption>
    </mediaobject>
  </figure>


  

